Quote: When the Canterbury Association ship the <i>Randolph</i> arrived at the Port of Lyttelton on 16th December 18950, John Stanley and his young wife Mary were aon board as immigrants. [44] The Canterbury Association provided free lodgings for one week in the immigration barracks constructed for new arrivals at Lyttelton with provisions.
